programme.title: The Bomber
programme.desc: Part 7 of this epic tale of war, love, betrayal, and sabotage. When Andrey, Katya, and Linko crash land in the field of battle, they find themselves in a struggle for survival that test the bonds of friendship.

programme.title: The Bomber
programme.desc: Part 8 of this epic tale of war, love, betrayal, and sabotage. When Andrey, Katya, and Linko crash land in the field of battle, they find themselves in a struggle for survival that test the bonds of friendship.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Tent City Jail, Phoenix, Arizona, USA
programme.desc: Old army tents left over from the Korean War house prisoners instead of cells. The Sheriff is a hard man who refuses to spend any more than he has to on his prisoners. Harassment and humiliation is a part of everyday life at Tent City.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Antanimora Prison, Madagascar
programme.desc: Desperate overcrowding, rats, and disease come standard in Antanimora Prison. Surrounded by the capital Antananarivo, it's bursting at the seams. It was originally built for 800 prisoners, but now it contains more than 3,000 prisoners.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: For almost two centuries, tourists have been flocking to the waters of Lake Champlain hoping against the odds to glimpse the lake monster they’ve affectionately dubbed Champ. Learn about one of the oldest monster legends in the world.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: The Mothman legend captivates tourists from all over the world, who pilgrimage to Point Pleasant, West Virginia, to visit sighting locations, question locals and tour the Mothman museum or buy Mothman memorabilia. The monster is now a local celebrity.

programme.title: Galapagos Realm of Giant Sharks
programme.desc: This film reconstructs the life of famed marine biologist and environmental pioneer Jacques Cousteau using a fascinating mix of wildlife footage, archive material and elaborate reenactments.

programme.title: Galapagos Realm of Giant Sharks
programme.desc: In the far reaches of the Galapagos archipelago there is a remote island - Darwin Island. Here, a mysterious parade of giant whale sharks passes, all pregnant females, about to give birth. What has drawn them here? Where are they going?

programme.title: Snake Boss
programme.desc: Julia is put to the test trying to catch on of Australia's fastest snakes. Barry gives Julia a tough decision to make. A keelback is on the loose. Finally, Johnny and Julia are faced with a grim situation.

programme.title: Snake Boss
programme.desc: Julia rescues a policeman from an unwelcome intruder. Johnny gets to go up against a venomous snake all on his own. And Julia gets to go explore at night in a leech infested forest.

programme.title: Superfish: Billfish
programme.desc: Narrated by David Attenborough. The Marlin is the biggest, fastest, and most dangerous gamefish in the sea. Award-winning filmmaker, Rick Rosenthal, spend two years traveling the globe in a quest to document the lives of these awe-inspiring predators.

programme.title: Superfish: Bluefin Tuna
programme.desc: Narrated by David Attenborough. It is a giant among fish, yet few have filmed it in the wild. Rick Rosenthal sets off to uncover the secrets of the legendary bluefin tuna, while documenting its place in the grand scheme of the vast marine ecosystem.

programme.title: Wildest Indochina: Cambodia: The Water Kingdom
programme.desc: Cambodia's wildlife and climate is ruled by the monsoon cycle. It is a wild land of extreme rains, raging rivers and flooding lakes that create great challenges for its animals, and a fine balance between seasons.

programme.title: Animal River Challenge: Eye of the Eagle
programme.desc: An alarm call goes out and monkeys of all types throw themselves off branches and out of trees to hide in terror. Overhead a giant eagle easily twists and turns through the treetops, hunting for any animal caught out in the open. The Harpy eagle hunts.

programme.title: Australia's Wild Places: The Coast of the Whalesharks
programme.desc: On the remote coastline of Australia’s northwest, there are great natural wonders to be found. Above the sea on this sunbaked coast, there is very little; only a sparse landscape shaped by the arid conditions. But here, the miracle reveals itself….

programme.title: Secrets of the Deep: Shipwreck Treasure
programme.desc: Treasure hunters scour the ocean floor in search of shipwrecks and lost riches. The waters off the Florida Keys still hold some of these riches, even a king’s ransom, just waiting to be found.

programme.title: Comfort Eating
programme.desc: Nick is on his home turf, Islington, eating his way around town. He stops at a few places, one with his comedy hero Bob Mortimer. He also arranges to meet his girlfriend for an anniversary dinner at their favourite restaurant...but will she turn up?

programme.title: Comfort Eating
programme.desc: After his break-up, Nick wakes up in Camden. To thank his friend for crashing on his sofa, Nick takes him to breakfast. Then, a liquid lunch at an underground speakeasy where he invents his own cocktail before sampling food stalls at a street market.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: On the Way to School
programme.desc: A freak farm accident is caught on CCTV and the team is scrambled to rescue the three young victims. Paramedic Andy fights to save a five-year-old boy run over on his way to school and there's a tricky rescue in a ravine in the Dales.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: DIY Gone Wrong
programme.desc: The Yorkshire Air Ambulance swoops onto a suburban bowling green to help a woman fighting to save her husband's life after a DIY accident, and in the Dales a cyclist goes into cardiac arrest after a wasp sting.

programme.title: Inside JFK's Assassination
programme.desc: A bodyguard, a photographer, a bystander, and the future widow of the President: on 22 November 1963, they were all in Dallas, and JFK’s assassination would forever be embedded in their memory. Relive that fateful day through their eyes.

programme.title: JFK's Women: The Scandals Revealed
programme.desc: John F. Kennedy, the charismatic president. However, with all that charm came a hidden life of reckless sexual adventure. He had a confirmed affair with Marilyn Monroe, and at least five of his endeavors posed a potential threat to national security.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: San Pedro Prison, La Paz, Bolivia
programme.desc: Imagine a prison so fierce that guards stay outside for fear of their lives. Inside, the prisoners are in control: murderers, violent offenders, drug bosses. The inmates rule and anarchy prevails. Only the strongest survive this lawless place.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Dallas County Jail, Dallas. Texas, USA
programme.desc: The Dallas County Jail in Texas - a supersized facility with beds for 7,100 inmates. The biggest threat in the prison? Turf wars. With the surplus of inmates, there is less space to divide up between them, leading to relentless gang warfare.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: What is it about sleepy Adams, Tennessee, that attracts tourists eager to visit graveyards, haunted caves and cabins, swap scary stories and try to summon the spirits of the dead? The legend of the Bell Witch and a 200-year old haunting are they key.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: A 19th century legend has put the town of Rhinelander, Wisconsin on the map, a must-visit location for those interested in American folklore and the supernatural, as Rhinelander is the home of the Hodag, a mythical beast transformed into a town mascot.

programme.title: Caught on Camera
programme.desc: Host Nick Wallis reveals some of the street crime captured by London's 100,000 CCTV cameras: Fights, robberies, drug crimes and a massive gun rampage.

programme.title: Moonwalkers
programme.desc: What if Apollo 11 never actually made it? What if, in reality, Stanley Kubrick secretly shot the famous images of the moon landing in a studio, working for the US administration? Feat Rupert Grint & Ron Perlman.

programme.title: Adult World
programme.desc: From the producer of Assassination Nation, this dark and racy satirical drama sees eccentric college graduate Amy (Emma Roberts: We’re the Millers) begrudgingly accept a job at a sex shop, all while she pursues a relationship with her teacher.

programme.title: SuperBob
programme.desc: When postman Robert is struck by a meteor, he is bestowed with super powers. 6 years later, Bob finally gets a day off from his superhero duties and tries to get a shot at love. Starring: Brett Goldstein, Catherine Tate, Natalia Tena.

programme.title: Moomins
programme.desc: Discover the magical world of the Moomins in the classic and universally-loved animation series. Join young Moomin, Moominpappa, Moominmamma and their friends Snufkin, Little My, Sniff and Snork Maiden in their exciting adventures in Moominvalley.

programme.title: The Christmas Consultant
programme.desc: This Lifetime Original Movie stars David Hasselhoff as a sought after consultant hired by a workaholic mother (Caroline Rhea) in an effort to get her and her family through the holidays.

programme.title: My Bakery in Brooklyn
programme.desc: Two cousins, two kinds of thinking, and a bakery for saving.

programme.title: Christmas in Wonderland
programme.desc: Starring Matthew Knight and Chris Kattan. Three children and their father move from California to Canada. When they go shopping at the mall, they find counterfeit cash, inadvertently help catch crooks, and make a discovery about Santa.

programme.title: Paper Heart
programme.desc: Charlyne Yi embarks on a quest across America to make a documentary about the one subject she doesn't fully understand: love.

programme.title: Scorched
programme.desc: In this crime caper set in a small deserted town, three mischievous bank employees all plan to rob the bank at the same time but they're unaware of what the others are up to. But needless to say, it's all a bit of a botched job!

programme.title: The Face of Love
programme.desc: A lonely widow begins a romance with an art teacher who looks just like her late husband but does not tell him of the resemblance. Starring: Annette Bening, Ed Harris, Robin Williams.

programme.title: The Adventurer: Curse of the Midas Box
programme.desc: Transporting you to a rambunctious realm of enchanting fantasy. When Mariah's little brother is kidnapped, he follows a trail of clues to discover a hidden realm of monsters, ancient secrets and a long-lost artefact. Feat: Michael Sheen & Sam Neill.

programme.title: Girl Most Likely
programme.desc: A failed New York playwright awkwardly navigates the transition from Next Big Thing to Last Year's News. Starring: Kristen Wiig, Annette Bening, Matt Dillon, Natasha Lyonne.

programme.title: Let Go
programme.desc: Featuring the king of comedy Kevin Hart, this hilarious, unconventional and heartfelt journey is all about love, loss and other felonies! Discontent parole officer Walter is struggling with the humdrums of married life.

programme.title: Cruel Intentions
programme.desc: Two vicious step-siblings of an elite Manhattan prep school make a wager: to deflower the new headmaster's daughter before the start of term. Starring: Sarah Michelle Gellar, Ryan Phillippe, Reese Witherspoon.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Slime People
programme.desc: The crew puts Commando Cody on trial for crimes against reality after watching the sixth episode of Radar Men while slime monsters invade Los Angeles in The Slime People.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Moon Zero Two
programme.desc: Moon Zero Two: The crew stages their own moon landing pageant as they watch the film about an astronaut hired to capture an asteroid made of sapphires.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Untamed Youth
programme.desc: Joel invents a pipe with a smoke detector and a sprinkler system built in for the invention exchange. The guys watch a 1950s teen flick about youths sentenced to manual labor at a cotton farm.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Untamed Youth
programme.desc: Joel invents a pipe with a smoke detector and a sprinkler system built in for the invention exchange. The guys watch a 1950s teen flick about youths sentenced to manual labor at a cotton farm.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Jungle Goddess
programme.desc: Jungle Goddess: An heiress stranded in Africa is made queen of the jungle in the feature film and Bela Lugosi stars in the short The Phantom Creeps.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Rocket Attack U.S.A.
programme.desc: Rocket Attack U.S.A.: The crew watches the second chapter of The Phantom Creeps and a film about an American spy sent to the Soviet Union to investigate a missile attack.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Lost Continent
programme.desc: A military team sent to search for a lost rocket ends up trapped on a mountain inhabited by dinosaurs in Lost Continent.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: King Dinosaur
programme.desc: In King Dinosaur, the crew pokes fun as scientists are terrorized by snakes, bugs, and dinosaurs on a newly discovered planet.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Black Scorpion
programme.desc: Giant scorpions rise out of a volcano and attack Mexico in The Black Scorpion.

programme.title: Giant Spider Invasion
programme.desc: Mike and the 'bots suffer through The Giant Spider Invasion .

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: City Limits
programme.desc: Set in the future, a teenage gang battles a corporation for control of an abandoned city in City Limits . Crow sings a song devoted to Kim Cattrall and the guys try their hand at a City Limits trivia game.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Indestructible Man
programme.desc: In Indestructible Man, a violent criminal named Butcher Benson is executed and becomes indestructible when he’s brought back to life. Butcher seeks revenge against those who caused his execution.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Abraxas: Guardian of the Universe
programme.desc: Abraxas, Guardian of the Universe, follows the heroic exploits of a galactic defender, played by Jesse Ventura, who comes to Earth to-wait, wait, that can't be right.

programme.title: Total Riff Off Episode 5: Animals Behaving Badly
programme.desc: From the stars of Mystery Science Theater 3000 comes RiffTrax, hilarious audio commentaries for your favorite - and not-so-favorite - movies!

programme.title: RiffTrax: Warriors of the Wasteland
programme.desc: So the Warriors of the Wasteland drive around in their admittedly sweet cars, sporting their admittedly heinous hairstyles, kinda resenting books and occasionally massacring an outpost of survivors.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Tourist Trap
programme.desc: Capitalizing on the widely-publicized series of unsolved murders that occurred at the Liberace Museum in Las Vegas in the late 1970s*, Tourist Trap is a slasher film with all the classic elements.

programme.title: The Mesa of Lost Women
programme.desc: Mesa of Lost Women! Not to be confused with the Plateau of Misplaced Babes, the Bayou of Wandering Broads, or the Tundra of Girlfriends Who Keep Trying to Get You to Ask for Directions but You're Simply Just Too Foolish and Proud.

programme.title: RiffTrax Live: Sharknado
programme.desc: From the moment it debuted, Sharknado was one of the most requested titles in RiffTrax history. It makes Jaws IV look like Jaws III, and Jaws III look like Jaws. You won't want to miss the chance to see Mike, Kevin, Bill, tackle Sharknado, live!

programme.title: RiffTrax: The Night That Dracula Saved The World
programme.desc: While The Night that Dracula Saved the World does not have Harvey Korman, or crappy animation, or an elderly wookie pleasuring itself, it does have Judd Hirsch. Please do not go into this special expecting not to see Judd Hirsch. Fair warning.

programme.title: RiffTrax: The Mesa of Lost Women: The Mesa of Lost Women (S1E59)
programme.desc: Mesa of Lost Women! Not to be confused with the Plateau of Misplaced Babes, the Bayou of Wandering Broads, or the Tundra of Girlfriends Who Keep Trying to Get You to Ask for Directions but You're Simply Just Too Foolish and Proud.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Voodoo Man: Voodoo Man
programme.desc: Young women are vanishing somewhere on the road that leads to the creepy old house of a deranged bachelor and his two lonely assistants. No one thinks to question the deranged bachelor and his two lonely assistants.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Future Zone: Future Zone
programme.desc: Mike, Kevin and Bill splashed a fresh coat o' mud onto their Chevy Blazer and made sure any and all gloves were firmly secured in an out-of-the-way box before hopping on the highway to the Future Zone!

programme.title: RiffTrax: Samurai Cop: Samurai Cop
programme.desc: Decapitations, explosions, poorly subbed in stunt doubles, mangled dialogue, prominent lion heads, and unfortunate banana hammocks abound in this extremely 80s-y 90s movie. Join Mike, Kevin, Bill, and Alfonso Rafael Federico Sebastian for Samurai Cop!

programme.title: Wonder Women
programme.desc: A fiendish supervillain is kidnapping star jai alai players in order to harvest their organs! Even more shocking, someone pitched that plot to a Hollywood executive and they said Yes, we'll make that movie!

programme.title: RiffTrax Presents: Scared to Death
programme.desc: Was there ever a more seminal film than Scared to Death? You heard me, seminal. It's a word. Look it up, it's not what you think.

programme.title: RiffTrax Presents: King of Kong Island
programme.desc: King of Kong Island is the action-packed tale of a scantily-clad jungle girl, some people who speak English without seeming to understand it and without bothering to move their lips, a mad scientist friend of theirs and their very many cigarettes.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Alien Outlaw
programme.desc: Predator costumes, Lash LaRue AND his fat hillbilly sidekick buddy from The Dark Power, an alien killed with a fishing hook, what more could anyone ask for. It's time for befuddlement and laughter, join Mike, Kevin and Bill for Alien Outlaw!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Ugly, Dirty and Good
programme.desc: The roaches try to break into the fridge but Oggy cuts off the cable that the insects were climbing to reach their objective. Joey falls and remains lying on the floor. But when Oggy is about to punish him, Joey smiles at him tenderly.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Just Married!
programme.desc: Jack is getting married, he chooses Oggy as his best man. Even though they haven't been invited, the cockroaches are of course attending the party! Jack gives an anti-cockroaches detector to Oggy to help him get rid of those damn insects.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories
programme.desc: Super-Noms' adventures continue! In this season, you will witness some unexpected comebacks of your favourite characters that will help Noms to fight the evil.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 7
programme.desc: In this new season, our superheroes return and so do their foes! You will see some acquaintances among the villains but their moves will be far from familiar ... However, Dr. Cheddar has something special to help Om Nom and Om Nelle in their adventures.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 8
programme.desc: Super-Noms always come to the rescue! However, in this season, rather than saving the whole city, they'll have to focus on their friends and protect them from the mischief!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 9
programme.desc: In this season, Super-Noms will discover that superpowers are not always helpful, and that kindness, bravery, and intelligence are the real gems that can solve any situation!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Basket Bunny / Bottle Racquet
programme.desc: Braianna is the star of her school basketball team but right in the middle of a game, she has to leave to take care of an intergalactic chicken ... / Fred wants to build a floating island made of bottles ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: The Day the Boys Stood Still / Mouse Trap
programme.desc: Fred tries to get Brains interested in his hobby – mud racing. In his attempt to convince her he awakens the demons of the mud. / Brains has to take care of Mr. Boots, a new recruit that is also a tiny mouse.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: King of the Sewer Bears / The Smelly Princess
programme.desc: Fred is named the King of the Sewer Bears due to his special birthmark. But the power is going to his head ... / Agent Brains has to protect princess Iria but her smell is so beguiling that you have to fulfil her every wish.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: The Dung Beetle / The Ride of Their Lives
programme.desc: Braianna is invited to a TV animal show but Corky is jealous and tries everything to stop her from going. / Fred and Sir Percival want to try out the new attraction in the amusement park. Friday is sad as he has to stay at home ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Return of the Dirt Demonds / The New Fred
programme.desc: Fred wants to make a monster film to impress Nora – and goes on a search for real monsters! Fred inadvertently hurts Nora with his words. He orders Friday to speak for him from now on ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Coach Dad / The Thing that Slept Over
programme.desc: Fred is not happy: His dad becomes the new gym teacher and all of Fred's classmates are exhausted! / Agent Brains investigates a slumber party to find out who has the energy-sucking leech Slimetra.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Egghead's Revenge / Surprise Day Off
programme.desc: Egghead wants to take revenge on Brains as she receives an award for being the smartest scientist. / All the teachers have been kidnapped by Potatoids – and have mutated into babies!

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Sewer Adventure!
programme.desc: Admiral Bubbles tricks Mom into believing she accidentally killed him. Horrified, she flushes him down the toilet, then quickly buys an identical fish to replace him with, hoping Beanie won't notice.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Goldfish Teriyaki!
programme.desc: A huge battle between Beanie and Admiral Bubbles in the kitchen results in the destruction of the oven. When Mom discovers this, she decides to use the money she was saving to buy a new bed to buy an oven instead.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Rescued!
programme.desc: In celebration of "Earth Day", Kevin Kelp, an ex- Greenspace activist, has converted the city's old incinerator into a recycling plant. But this is a great disappointment to Admiral Bubbles, who hates to see the old incinerator go to waste.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Stinker!
programme.desc: Inspired by the horrible mess that Beanie has cooked up for his mother's breakfast, Admiral Bubbles decides to cook up a garbage monster, bringing it to life to do his evil bidding and to terrorize the town.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Forgetful Fish!
programme.desc: Beanie and Elwood have done their school science report on earthquakes, discovering that the town is built on a fault line. Admiral Bubbles realizes that with a simple machine serving as a catalyst, he could easily destroy the entire town.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Icing On The Cake!
programme.desc: It's Beanie's birthday, and he is looking forward to his party, until he discovers that his Mom decorated the apartment in "Cute Little Bunnies". With guests starting to arrive, and certain that he will die of embarrassment, he asks the goldfish for help.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: The Secret Terractor!
programme.desc: During summer vacation, Beanie is spending two weeks on his Grandpa and Grandma's farm, and brings Admiral Bubbles along so he can keep an eye on him.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Spaceballs
programme.desc: Invincible United’s unscrupulous striker, Skarra, kidnaps the Professor and forces the fitness genius to help him outdo his enemies.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: El Sound Of Silencio
programme.desc: Supa Strikas are annihilated by Orion’s amazing airborne moves. Coach takes them to a space facility to train in a magnetic levitation chamber.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Amal Three's a Crowd
programme.desc: Rival team, Invincible United, orchestrate a fan ban for upcoming Supa Strikas matches! El Matador doesn’t think it’s a big deal, but come crunch time, he cannot perform in the empty stadium!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Bad Altitude
programme.desc: Supa Strikas get the fright of their lives upon hearing that Sultans have signed famed triplets, the Amal 3. They are said to have a psychic connection that cannot be beaten!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: The Lost Star
programme.desc: Funky Cool Joe gets into the rhythm before every game with his favourite song. But when the evil Toni Vern switches his record, the star player can’t understand why he’s useless on the field!

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: War of the Clones
programme.desc: Bernie comes up with a few Zig-clones. These replicas get hammered in Zig's place but always come back empty-handed. Before long, a horde of uncontrollable clones has invaded the lagoon - and things go crazy!

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Manic Mermaid
programme.desc: Another mermaid suddenly shows up in the lagoon. Marina is none too happy about this intruder. Sharko gets all confused, he doesn't know which is which and Zig takes advantage of the confusion in order to grab at least one of the mermaids.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Sea's Up
programme.desc: The lagoon's waters suddenly rise and almost entirely engulf the island. Sharko and Marina take advantage of this to visit the island but Marina gets lost. She leaves a trail of coconuts behind so Sharko can find her, but Bernie outwits her….

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Hair Story
programme.desc: Marina's getting dolled up for a visit to the opera. Alas, her Octopus-Hairdresser cuts half her hair off by mistake! She has to find a wig, fast! Sharko whizzes to the island and shaves every creature he meets. But the only fur she fancies is Zig's!

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Toys Attack!
programme.desc: A cargo ship runs aground on the beach, its hold loaded with toys. Zig will turn them into inventions so he can get his mermaid: a spinning top becomes a propelling device, a croquet set, used as weapons, soap bubbles and even a giant robot!

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Sharko and His Folks
programme.desc: Sharko finally decides to declare his love to Marina. But when he pulls out the engagement ring he plans to give her, his parents show up for a surprise visit! Not easy for Sharko to present his adored Mermaid to these two.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Tiny Tyrant
programme.desc: Bernie concocts a magic potion to make you incredibly strong... but keeps it for himself. He wields his new power over Zig, over Sharko, even over Neptune. In short: he's the STRONGEST of them all! Is there any way to get him step off the throne?

programme.title: The Wiggle's Present: Baby Antonio's Circus: Episode 3

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: When Nordic Gods Attack
programme.desc: With only a handful of life points remaining and the Nordic God, Thor, staring down at him, Jack gets set to take on his next opponent - Team Ragnarok's Broder!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Tricking the Trickster
programme.desc: After swooping in take on Team Ragnarok's Broder, Crow finds himself battling two Nordic Gods  Thor and Loki! Can Crow defeat these two dynamos, or will this dynamic duo prove to be too much for Crow and his battle-tested Blackwings?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Yusei's Last Stand
programme.desc: With the tournament on the line, Yusei must find a way to defeat Halldor before the three Nordic Gods knock his life points down to nothing!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Fight to the Finish Line
programme.desc: It's the exciting conclusion to the semifinal battle between Team Ragnarok and Team 5D's! Can Yusei Fudo muster a miracle comeback against Team Ragnarok's Halldor?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Beginning of the End

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dawn of the Machines
programme.desc: It's one down and two to go for Team 5D's as Jack and his mighty Red Nova Dragon get set to take on and take out Primo and Jakob of Team New World!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Against All Odds

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: For Synchro's Sake

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Fight for the Future

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Escape the Escape Room - Part 2
programme.desc: The investigation continues at the escape room and a certain spirit attempts to tug at Sean's clothing. Will he finally survive the escape room?

programme.desc: Sean heads to Leeds and investigates Abbey House Museum among a maze of Victorian streets and shops. Who will he bump into tonight and what secrets does this location hold?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Lights Out at Abbey House Museum - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation at Abbey House Museum and ventures outside into the monastery ruins. Will he find the ghostly monk tonight?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: The Evil Cook at The Shakespeare Pub
programme.desc: Sean explores The Shakespeare pub in Manchester and meets Flecky Bennett to investigate claims dating back hundreds of years, about an evil chef that is haunting the pub.

programme.desc: Sean heads to Stanton Moor, Derbyshire and encounters a portal to the spirit dimension within a mystical stone circle, used for witchcraft and occult practices. With no outside interference, the activity is off the scale.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo
programme.desc: Buried under the location Sean investigates tonight, is the bones of the deceased and it appears that they are at unrest. Will Sean solve the mystery of who is haunting this location?

programme.desc: Witchcraft, demons and ghosts have all been reported to haunt these caves. Sean investigates this network of tunnels deep underground and uncovers that all is not as it seems. This is not a day out at the seaside at Beech Caves.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Multiple ghostly sightings have been reported that could be connected to the close, but what will Sean and Bex encounter during the day for a special Ghost Dimension Lock Down investigation?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension's Bex and Sean investigate Norris Green Mansion. A 17th Century building, which is believed to hold some of the most haunted spirits in Liverpool. Will they make contact its ghostly entities tonight?

programme.desc: Ghost Dimension's Bex and Sean head to New Mills and investigate a home situated on the grounds of death and destruction from the bombings of WW2. Will any of the spirits lost in this disaster come forward and make contact during the investigation today?

programme.desc: We want to believe that all women would give their lives to protect their children. But there are horrifying cases when a mother will turn against her natural instinct and kill her own flesh and blood.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The mind of a female killer is shaped by a complex cocktail of influences. Do people become that way, driven by horrendous events in their lives? Or are some killers born bad?

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Blood ties are strong ties, sometimes strong enough to pull a person into a murderous conspiracy. When a family member wields his or her power, the result can be death.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The path towards revenge can sometimes lead to murder. It can be quick, fiery and violent. It can also be a dish served cold, the product of a calm, calculated plot.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: While their sisters chose a life of sensible, suburban motherhood, these deadly women chose a life of crime. They lived with the thrills, the danger and the deadly consequences of being outlaws.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Greed is one of the oldest motives for murder, and these deadly women are no exception: they’ll do anything to satisfy their need for cash. This is the dangerous world of the fortune hunters.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Sometimes, when a man and a woman unite, a terrible urge for destruction can awaken in them both. Happy couples become deadly teams, intent on one goal: murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: While marriage is meant to be for life, it often ends in divorce. These wives took their marriages vow seriously: "till death do us part.".

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These women never get their hands dirty: no blood touched them because they manipulate others to kill for them...but they didn't get away.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Women who kill husbands, lovers, rivals and parents will shock society. But a very special horror is reserved for women who will kill their own.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A lovely lady with an innocent smile, kind eyes, a charming personality? No one would suspect a woman like that would murder. These women don’t look or behave like killers.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The heaviest judgments of convicted killers are reserved for those who committed premeditated murder. These women plot and plan. They know the consequences of their actions, but still they go forward to kill.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Under His Control
programme.desc: These are love stories with bleak, bloody endings. Blinded by desire, obsessed and malleable, some women fall into lethal relationships with dangerous, controlling men.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Secrets and Lies
programme.desc: Behind their friendly smiles, deadly women hide histories of bloodshed and murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love Gone Wrong
programme.desc: Love can be beautiful, love can be blind and love can be deadly. Desire and jealousy are powerful forces driving women to dark and horrifying places in their minds.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Married to Murder
programme.desc: To the outside world, their marriages seemed happy. But behind closed doors, there was no domestic bliss. These women wanted out, but getting a divorce wasn’t their preferred option.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Teen Killers
programme.desc: They were too young to drink or vote but they were not too young to commit the most brutal of crimes. Some were driven by pure curiosity: how would it feel to take a life?

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love to Death
programme.desc: Love and money are a beautiful marriage, for the lucky ones they create a life of happiness and ease. Unless the love is of money, the bride is a killer, and the groom their victim.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Kill Their Own
programme.desc: A mother's most basic instinct is to protect her children, to put their needs above her own desire for money, freedom and men. But these deadly women break that sacred bond when they turn against that natural instinct and kill their own offspring.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Driven to Kill
programme.desc: A serial rapist targeted women. His dark urges raged out of control and led him to murder. He followed a path so random it was impossible to trace, and all that tied him to his crimes were his access to the highways and a bizarre sexual fetish.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Obsession
programme.desc: Power is a responsibility as well as a privilege. But in the wrong hands, power can corrupt. For former Deputy Attorney General for the State of Delaware, losing sight of his sworn oath to uphold justice could prove lethal.

programme.title: The FBI Files: First and Kennedy Street Crew
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise
programme.desc: Banks use a variety of devices to discourage would-be robbers: security cameras, silent alarms, and exploding dye packs. But when an elusive bank robber targeted Seattle's banks, none of these precautions were effective.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Trail
programme.desc: The disappearance of young women triggered a search that spanned the Pacific Northwest. A massive media campaign failed to locate the drifter, who first charmed then killed them. As investigators followed his trail, he always stayed one step ahead.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Predator
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Dishonored
programme.desc: Shirley Russell was determined enough to reach the rank of Captain in the United States Marine Corps. When this officer turned up missing, her colleagues refused to believe she had gone AWOL. It was unclear whether Captain Shirley Russell was alive.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Millionaire Murder
programme.desc: A businessman went to Florida to make one last deal before he retired-he never returned home to his millions. Authorities examined who was closest to him and who stood to gain from his disappearance. But this time conventional rules didn't apply.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Business
programme.desc: Many escape the poverty of India to start new lives in the United States. One turned the American dream into a nightmare. People started turning up dead in New York's Indian community-authorities struggled to link fraud and murder to a powerful man.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Temple of Fear
programme.desc: In Miami, the discovery of a mutilated body sent investigators on the trail of a deadly cult. But agents found a wall of silence around the cult's members. Potential witnesses, terrified of reprisals, refused to talk.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Silent Strike
programme.desc: Money may not be the root of all evil, but for some men, a million dollars is enough to justify murder. Even men sworn to uphold the law can sometimes be tempted.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Stranger
programme.desc: The body of a young woman found burned in a truck launched a manhunt to find her killer. When more bodies began to turn up across the country, the FBI believed the cases were linked. Investigators had a suspect. They just couldn't find him.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Backstage Murder
programme.desc: In the 1980's, two partners created a nightclub that would bring them wealth and international fame. The male strip club phenomenon promised female patrons fun and excitement. But the bright lights hid a dark side.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Under Fire
programme.desc: A series of armored car heists and bloody shoot-outs shocked law enforcement. The brutal violence of the crimes suggested a motive more complex than greed. When the robbers started targeting police, the FBI took charge.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Manhunt
programme.desc: A killer was on the loose in one of America's most popular tourist destinations. Armed and desperate, he evaded law enforcement at every turn. As the Fourth of July weekend quickly approached, thousands of people became potential targets.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hunter's Target
programme.desc: Over a thousand hunting accidents are reported in the United States each year. Fewer than ten percent of them are fatal. But when one hunter's death seemed suspicious, the FBI was called in to investigate.

programme.title: The FBI Files: No Remorse
programme.desc: A burning body in a dark alley shed light on a cold-blooded killer. His partners in crime would tell the story, if they lived. In the underworld of the drug trade, even a childhood friend can quickly become an enemy.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The C-11 Squad
programme.desc: New York City is not stranger to gang violence. But when a 12-year-old child was kidnapped, the gangs had crossed a line. Law enforcement raced to find the missing boy before it was too late.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Polly Klaas: Kidnapped
programme.desc: On October 1, 1993, a stranger abducted 12-year-old Polly Klaas during a slumber party in her home.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Above the Law
programme.desc: California Highway Patrolman George Gwaltney discovered the body of 23-year-old Robin Bishop near her car on a remote desert highway.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Human Prey
programme.desc: Thomas Dillon killed five outdoorsmen at random over a period of three years in rural southern Ohio. After a tip led the FBI to the murder weapon, ballistic testing made a match.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Death in Alaska
programme.desc: The day began like any other for Cheryl and Paul Chapman, until the silence of a peaceful Sunday morning was shattered with a phone call.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Paradise
programme.desc: It should have been Shangri-La, but when bad blood developed, piracy took over and the only law was the law of the jungle.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Crazy Don
programme.desc: To the FBI, he was believed to be the boss of New York's most powerful mafia organization: the Genovese crime family. Was Gigante crazy or was his behavior a shrewd attempt to disguise his position as a ruthless mafia boss?

programme.title: Children of the Wind
programme.desc: Children of the Wind tells the story of the Bonaire windsurfers, a group of native Caribbean kids, who under the mentorship of Elvis Martinus, founder of the Bonaire Aquaspeed windsurfing club, overcame insuperable odds.

programme.title: Chapters
programme.desc: Chapters is a collection of stories told by a world class group of surfers. The cast of eight was selected to balance and bridge the gap between loggers and high performance longboarders.

programme.title: Castles In the Sky
programme.desc: It begins with a dream. A vision seeded in your mind. But the next step is the one that counts. The first step. Onto the plane. Into the sky. From that moment on, the journey takes on a life of its own.

programme.title: Alternative Surf Craft
programme.desc: Alternative Surf Craft profiles the surfers on the edge of the sport. These surfers carve their own path riding unique and alternative surf craft.

programme.title: Absolute Mexico
programme.desc: Absolute Mexico The Directors Cut - includes bonus footage not included in the original release. See insane tube rides; interviews with top pro-surfers and gorgeous footage of one of the biggest days ever filmed at Puerto Escondido.

programme.title: Absolute Chile
programme.desc: In this follow-up to Absolute Mexico, director Joshua Pomer explores the northern coast of Chile. There we find an all-star crew heading south for some big wave tow surfing.

programme.title: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory
programme.desc: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory is presented in a dream like structure with no distracting titles letting the visual imagery speak freely to your surfing soul and wanderlust.

programme.title: Chill: Crashed Ice Tour, Canada & Leo Slemett
programme.desc: Chill moves to the winter sports this week as we head to Niagara Falls, Canada where they are hosting the opening round of the Crashed Ice Tour.

programme.title: Chill: Wakeboarding Legend, Harley Clifford & Kiteboarding Elite, Liam Whaley
programme.desc: This week on CHILL we take a tour through one of the world's best board sports on the water with Harley Clifford. And we witness kiteboarding at its elite level with Spain's Liam Whaley and others.

programme.title: Chill: Cold Water Classic, Canada & World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia
programme.desc: Jarrad Howse takes Chill to the hidden surfing destination of Tofino in Canada. Cold, wet and windy but better yet, sublime surf! We catch up with the Pro's at the Cold Water Classic.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Women's Waterski Jumping, Australia & World Cup Waterski Slalom, Indonesia
programme.desc: This week on Chill, it's water skiing around the world, we're at the jumping in Australia and the slalom in Palembang. We check out PKRA Mexico, then catch up with surfing sensations, Courtney Cologue and Sage Erickson.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Indonesia & Longboard Pro Circuit, China
programme.desc: We look at the skills required and the thrills delivered by the wave that stands as the king of them all - the mighty Barrel. The Longboard Pro Circuit in China is our next destination where we hang out with Kassia Meador and Darcy Liu..

programme.title: Chill: Swatch Pro Tour, France & World Cup Waterski Jumping, Australia
programme.desc: Chill joins the girls of the Swatch Pro Tour in South West France, the top riders and local talent in the freestyle section of the PKRA event in Mexico and the men of world cup waterski jumping in Australia.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia & Kitesurfing World Tour, Italy
programme.desc: The very best in Women's wakeboarding as the IWWF comes to Mandurah in Australia. The beautiful Italian Island of Sicily plays host to the Kitesurfing world Tour.

programme.title: Chill: Action Sports Game, Australia & Women's World Longboard Championship, China
programme.desc: Chill heads down under for some water ski-jumping with the Men's Action Tricks Comp and Women's Ski Jump. We take an in-depth look at the Women's longboard Championships in the South China Sea.

programme.title: Chill: Waterski Jump Legend, Freddy Krueger & Women Longboard Professionals, China
programme.desc: This week we will travel to Western Australia to catch up with the Waterski Jump Legend Freddy Krueger. Style, elegance and a hard edge of competition combine in China as we watch some of the best women longboard professionals.

programme.title: Chill: World Kitesurfing Champion, Youri Zoon
programme.desc: Chill heads to Rio to follow some of the biggest names in the Surfing arena. An inside look with World Kitesurfing Champion Youri Zoon and an intimate training session with a bunch of Wakeboarders.

programme.title: Chill: Freddy Krueger, Wakeboard World Cup Australia
programme.desc: Freddy "The Nightmare" Krueger is the undisputed ski jumping legend. Chill gets up close and personal to discover his drive and passion which ultimately keeps him striving for perfection.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia & Kitesurfing World Tour, Morocco
programme.desc: We are on the waters of Mandurah, Australia for the men's finals at the IWWF Wakeboard World. Morocco is our next destination for the kitesurf world tour, and we profile Harley Clifford.

programme.title: Minds in the Water
programme.desc: The story of one surfer's international journey to help protect dolphins, whales and their ocean environment. Shot on location in Australia, the Galapagos, Chile and Japan, it captures a key moment in one person's life when apathy is no longer an option.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Missing Person
programme.desc: Tragedy unfolds at Westbrook Beach when lifeguards are unable to locate a missing man. The man will be deemed lost at sea if he isn’t found soon, so senior lifeguard Ant takes charge.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: The Festive Season Kicks Off
programme.desc: Durban, South Africa is a hot spot for vacationers during the busy summer season. The season starts on high alert when senior lifeguard Sihle rescues a bather caught in a rip current.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Busiest Day of the Year
programme.desc: New Year’s is the busiest day of the year in Durban. Crowds arrive in hopes that the sea, soft sand and sunshine will cure their hangovers. It's a day of frivolity and endless mishaps.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Powercraft
programme.desc: It's December 31 — a good day for lifeguard trainee Penny to face her fear of big waves. All eyes are on her as she paddles into some of the biggest waves of the season.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Mass Rescue
programme.desc: There's pandemonium at the Wedge when a flash rip sweeps 150 bathers — most of whom can’t swim — off of the sand bank and into deep, treacherous water.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: African Christmas
programme.desc: The fun and festivity of Christmas Day are put on hold after a mass blue bottle jellyfish attack. Lifeguards are forced to close Battery Beach and Country Club.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Day of Reconciliation
programme.desc: The Day of Reconciliation — the first big public holiday of the festive season — starts off damp and overcast. Undeterred, 150,000 vacationers flock to the beaches.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Shark Attack
programme.desc: Five bathers are bitten by an unknown sea creature at the Bay of Plenty, breaking the festive mood and creating a mass panic. Could this be a shark attack?

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Ragers Start the Party
programme.desc: High school graduates, or "ragers," spill onto Umhlanga Beach after partying all night. This beach is plagued by hidden rocks and strong rips — a disaster cocktail for party animals.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Most Dangerous Beach
programme.desc: Senior lifeguard Luthuli and his “men of steel” work the Wedge, Durban’s most dangerous beach. The shoreline has an unstable sand bank with dangerous holes on either side.

programme.title: Way of the Ocean: Australia
programme.desc: Way of the Ocean Australia explores the connection between man and sea through a visual feast of poetic motion. This wave rich continent provides a breathtaking backdrop to some of the best surfing found on the planet.

programme.title: Surfing Elite (2013)
programme.desc: Surfing Elite The Pro Tape is a surfing movie dedicated to the biggest names in professional surfing. This is the Surfing Elite. These are the shakers and movers of our sport and for good reason.

programme.title: Laurel & Hardy: Any Old Port!
programme.desc: In need of money, Ollie signs Stan up for a prize fight against an old nemesis.

programme.title: Laurel & Hardy: Block Heads
programme.desc: Unaware that the Great War has ended, Stan remains faithfully at his post for twenty years.

programme.title: Laurel & Hardy: Busy Bodies

programme.desc: JT has got his licence. He’s got a steady girlfriend in Liberty, who happens to be Student Council President. So why is he feeling anything but a “man”? Because Liberty’s in control.

programme.title: Degrassi: The Next Generation: Weddings, Parties, Anything
programme.desc: After all the craziness of last year, Craig has one overriding goal: no drama. He’s focused on his friends, his family, his studies, and his band – a reconstituted Downtown Sasquatch but no Spinner - a new addition is rocking the drum-kit….

programme.title: Degrassi: The Next Generation: I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For
programme.desc: After proving he’s still got talent on the hardwood, Jimmy is invited to try out for the Wheelchair Basketball Association’s Junior Team. It’s Jimmy’s second chance at athletic stardom, and an opportunity to make his father proud.

programme.title: Degrassi: The Next Generation: Turned Out, Pt. 1
programme.desc: As Liberty’s pregnancy enters its sixth month, she and JT are forced to face reality: even though no longer a couple, they have to deal with the pregnancy.

programme.title: Degrassi: The Next Generation: Turned Out, Pt. 2
programme.desc: Desperate for cash, JT has stolen drugs from the pharmacy… He becomes entangled in a web between his boss, the drug dealer and the police.

programme.title: Degrassi: The Next Generation: Tell it to My Heart
programme.desc: Someone’s definitely interested in Marco. But as it turns out, Tim is interested in Marco, but not for the expected reason. Tim knows Marco is gay, and has been struggling with how to come out to his friends and family.

programme.title: Degrassi: The Next Generation: Redemption Song
programme.desc: The one-year anniversary of the school shooting is approaching and everyone’s feeling the weight of it. Not least of whom is Spinner Mason, still persona non grata.
Tonight is the premiere of “Jay and Silent Bob Go Canadian, Eh” and with many of the students and faculty on the guest list, it’s like the whole school is gripped in movie premiere fever!

Paige wakes Alex up in her bed – Paige spent the night on the floor – and as the two girls awkwardly prepare for school, they try to avoid the elephant in the room. As in, that they KISSED last night. What happened?

programme.title: Degrassi: The Next Generation: Together Forever
programme.desc: Craig bursts into rehearsal with the good news – they’ve been accepted to perform at a Northern Sounds Showcase. The band is NOT so into it at first – music is Craig’s dream, not theirs.

programme.title: Crime Invasion: Organized Car Crime Gangs
programme.desc: This episode reveals the story of “Operation Aberdale,” a Metropolitan Police initiative that jailed ten of the UK's most prolific luxury car thieves.

programme.title: Crime Invasion: Street Gangs
programme.desc: In this episode, "Crime Invasion" investigates the complicated internal workings of violent street and drug gangs that plunge Birmingham's inner city into chaos.

programme.title: Crime Invasion: Asian Heroin Gangs
programme.desc: UK heroin gangs control the whole dispersion network, from importation to street-level dealing. "Crime Invasion" goes undercover to film drug deals in West London.

programme.title: Crime Invasion: Snakeheads & Triads
programme.desc: How did 58 Chinese nationals end up dead in the back of a tomato truck? Rageh travels to Dover to investigate the gangs behind illegal immigration operations into the UK.

programme.title: True Nordic Crime: The Vanished Mother
programme.desc: Young mother of three children disappears after a night out with her best friend. She did not return home to her children the following day and was nowhere to be found. Her family and friends knew something was terribly wrong.

programme.title: True Nordic Crime: Night Horrors
programme.desc: A woman asleep in her living room is brutally attacked with a hammer in the middle of the night. Even though one of her daughter witnesses the attack through a glass door she can't help her screaming mother because the perpetrator locked the doors.

programme.title: True Nordic Crime: The Amphetamine Factory
programme.desc: At one point the biggest and most technically advanced Amphetamine Factory in Europe was in Iceland. It was run by ex-prisoners and one of them had studied chemistry at University level while in jail.

programme.title: Interpol Investigates: One Way Ticket
programme.desc: A boat carrying over 300 illegal Chinese immigrants runs aground in New York Harbor. Several die, others are taken into custody by INS officials and NYPD. The case leads investigators to the gangs of Chinatown.

programme.title: Interpol Investigates: The Missing Link
programme.desc: A small automotive repair shop explodes in the early morning hours in Managua, Nicaragua, killing two people and shattering a peaceful neighborhood.

programme.title: Interpol Investigates
programme.desc: Mireille Ballestrazzi is in charge of the Art Theft Squad of the French National Police. Her efforts to track down thieves who took five paintings by Jean Baptiste Camille Carot lead her into collaboration with Interpol.

programme.title: 72 Hours: Kidnapped
programme.desc: A wealthy Asian girl is kidnapped in Vancouver. When the kidnappers make the fateful error of using the young girl’s cell phone, police are able to track their movements and capture the assailants.

programme.title: 72 Hours: Monster of Miramichi
programme.desc: Firemen are called to a blaze and discover two sisters, one dead and the other on death's door. Detectives learn that a man snuck in and brutally sexually assaulted the sisters before setting fire to the house.

programme.title: 72 Hours: The Violinist
programme.desc: Surgically clean body parts start turning up on a highway. Stranger still, they have been drained of every drop of blood.

programme.title: 72 Hours: Betrayed
programme.desc: 19 year old Greg Parsons is convicted of brutally murdering his mother mainly on evidence of the audio tape of a song he'd written, "Kill your Parents".

programme.title: 72 Hours: The Great Despisers
programme.desc: A 19 year old man comes home one night to discover that his family had all been savagely murdered. Could it be the insurance money and a movie called "The Great Despisers" that motivated the killers to perpetrate such violence?

programme.title: 72 Hours: Faith Healer
programme.desc: A trucker at a roadside rest station discovers the fully clothed body of a dead East Indian woman.

programme.title: Alaska State Troopers: Drunk and Dangerous
programme.desc: Danger is on the rise as flooding takes over south-central Alaska. A 17-inch storm surge and high winds have left thousands in danger and even uprooted residential homes.

programme.title: Alaska State Troopers: Crystal Meth Compund
programme.desc: Like a scene from an action movie, Troopers silently and swiftly surround the home of a well-known criminal suspected of hiding stolen guns.

programme.title: Alaska State Troopers: Trooper Stalker
programme.desc: Talk about a long commute! Trooper Massey must drive to the airport, catch an airplane and be picked up by a patrol boat to get from St. Mary's to Alakanuk.

programme.title: Alaska State Troopers: Deep Woods Standoff
programme.desc: Not only when standing in the line of fire during traffic pullovers, but also during undercover decoy operations, troopers must remain vigilant in all corners of the state so they aren't caught on their heels and in a deadly predicament.

programme.title: Hard Time
programme.desc: When a crime happens in Vegas, the criminal stays in Vegas, at one of the largest county jails in the United States. The Clark County Detention Center is in the heart of downtown Las Vegas, blocks from the Strip, and it’s a co-ed jail.

programme.title: Hard Time
programme.desc: Down the street from the Clark County Detention Center is the District Court. Each week hundreds of inmates are collected from their jail cells and herded through the underground network of tunnels that connect the two buildings, to face a Judge.

programme.title: Hard Time
programme.desc: The Clark County Detention Center in Las Vegas handles more than 80,000 people each year. For many inmates, jail is a harsh wake-up call and a one-time stop. But for 1000's of offenders hooked on drugs and alcohol, CCDC becomes a revolving door.

programme.title: FBI: Criminal Pursuit
programme.desc: The body of a toddler girl is found in a box in a waterway in Galveston, Texas. Investigators nickname her Baby Grace… and must rely on the FBI to figure out the mystery child’s identity… and why she was killed.

programme.title: FBI: Criminal Pursuit
programme.desc: When Brian Wilson’s wife, Inga, goes missing after a late night run to the store, no one is expecting her body to show up 15 miles away from their home.

programme.title: FBI: Criminal Pursuit
programme.desc: When the body of a little boy floats up in Waldport, Oregon, the FBI sets out on a search for his missing family. One by one, their murdered bodies appear…leading agents that much closer to their killer.

programme.title: Killer Kids
programme.desc: Prejudice and intolerance affect our society. For some youths religious groups, linguistic and ethnic difference, or even sexual orientation can become pretexts for violence.

programme.title: Killer Kids
programme.desc: For some youngsters family pressure can sometimes become intolerable. The insufferable situation can be due to abuse, hate, money or perhaps a disagreement within the family. Many children or adolenscents can only see one possible solution... murder.

programme.title: Forensic Investigators: Paul Snabel
programme.desc: When Paul Snabel didn’t return home for over a week in November 1989, his flatmate became concerned and reported him missing.

programme.title: Forensic Investigators: Truong
programme.desc: On 29 April 1996, Le Anh Tuan was kidnapped by three men from his Melbourne home. In broad daylight, neighbours watched as he was bundled into the boot of a car. His captors later demanded a $400,000 ransom for his safe return.

programme.title: Outlaw Empires
programme.desc: From the 1800s to the early 1970s, Irish street gangs waged war for control of Boston’s underworld. By 1972, they had called a truce. One man, James “Whitey” Bulger, emerged from that truce to become a lethal and legendary force.

programme.title: Some Girls
programme.desc: On the eve of his wedding, a successful writer travels across the country to meet up with ex-lovers in an attempt to make amends for past relationship transgressions. Starring: Adam Brody, Kristen Bell, Zoe Kazan.

programme.title: Paper Year
programme.desc: Young newlyweds encounter a series of challenges during the first year of their marriage. Feat: Andie MacDowell.

programme.title: Proof Of Love
programme.desc: A female scientist conducts an experiment to find proof that her boyfriend is "the one.".

programme.title: Elsa And Fred
programme.desc: A withdrawn senior experiences life in new ways when he begins spending time with the free-spirited woman who lives across the hall. Starring: Shirley MacLaine, Christopher Plummer, Marcia Gay Harden.

programme.title: A Random Encounter
programme.desc: What seems to be a chance encounter one day at a coffee shop leads to a full-fledged romance, but the couple must fight for their relationship to survive the craziness that is show business. Starring: Meghan Markle, Sean Young, Michael Rady.

programme.title: Before You Say I Do
programme.desc: George wants to marry Jane, but she swore off marriage after her first husband broke her heart. After wishing he had met Jane before she got married, George winds up ten years in the past.

programme.title: Accidentally Engaged
programme.desc: Famous actor Chas Hunter and aspiring actress Clarissa Byers agree to fake an engagement to improve both their reputations. However, playing pretend starts to feel all too real as the two start to fall for one another.

programme.title: Not Another Happy Ending
programme.desc: When a troubled editor discovers that his only successful author is blocked, he knows that he needs to do something about it. Starring: Karen Gillan, Stanley Weber, Iain De Caestecker, Gary Lewis.

programme.title: My Girlfriend's Boyfriend
programme.desc: Jesse meets Ethan, someone she could finally fall in love with, but then she meets Troy, and now she has a dilemma. Starring: Christopher Gorham, Alyssa Milano, Michael Landes.

programme.title: Happiness Is A Four Letter Word
programme.desc: Perfectionist Nandi seems to have the New South African Dream life in her grasp, black female partner in a major firm, marriage, the perfect house - but it all goes up in flames before the wedding.

programme.title: 4 Wedding Planners
programme.desc: When Lily goes home to Hawaii, she wants to help save her family's wedding planning business, even when her ex-boyfriend shows up as a new client.

programme.title: Under the Mistletoe
programme.desc: Starring Jaime Ray Newman, Michael Shanks, and Conan Graham. At Christmas, the tables turn on a selfless single mom when a local radio station takes over her love life after an innocent call from her 8-year-old son.

programme.title: Hollidaysburg
programme.desc: A former prom king and his high school classmate begin an unlikely romance when they return from college on their first holiday break. From the filmmakers behind BREAKUP AT A WEDDING.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Gravity

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Love on the Run
programme.desc: Today Dog finds himself looking for more than one fugitive. He starts the day looking for a woman who has skipped out on her court date. But he soon learns that she has teamed up with a woman whose criminal exploits have attracted the local media.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Jump Start
programme.desc: Dog gave a break to a young man with a drug problem who promised to enter drug rehab. But this commitment to rehabilitation seems to have ended when he bolted from the car on the way to the drug treatment center and went on the run.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Ice Man
programme.desc: Dog's latest fugitive doesn't think small when it comes to illegal drugs: he was carrying almost a pound of meth when he was arrested. Now he's on the run with his pregnant girlfriend on the high plains of Colorado.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Trouble in Paradise
programme.desc: Dog is back in Hawaii and tracking a dangerous fugitive through the jungles of the Big Island. Their prey is being protected by a ring of family and friends that Dog must forcefully confront to bring in his man.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Girl Power
programme.desc: When Dog decides to spend the day caring for his newest granddaughter, Beth enlists the girls to hunt down a female fugitive. Heading into a dangerous part of town the ladies will use their feminine wiles to track this mother gone wrong.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Prodigal Son
programme.desc: Dog and his old friends, Tim Chapman and Sonny Westbrook are riding with the team, so their target, a thief with violent tendencies, is out of luck. When Dog learns that the fugitive is also a disrespectful son, he is more motivated to find his man.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Family Ties
programme.desc: Dog doesn't have the whole team today and he's got to catch a fugitive with a record of criminal assault. But when Dog finds the fugitive's former girlfriend, she thinks he isn't dangerous at all.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Special Delivery
programme.desc: For months, this fugitive has been stringing Leland along with a series of barely believable excuses. Out of patience, Leland calls in the Big Dog. The whole team heads out to put pressure on the family and friends of the fugitive.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Surface Scratches
programme.desc: Dog's latest quarry is running from abuse and assault charges. As Dog investigates, he discovers that this fugitive has gamed the system by jumping from one bond, and one bondsman, to another.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Great Debate
programme.desc: When the co-signer of a bond is also romantically involved with the defendant, sometimes the bondman is put in the middle of a lover's quarrel.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Facebooked
programme.desc: Dog is in Denver helping Bobby Brown to track down a fugitive with a long rap sheet. But unfortunately they have no picture of the felon to work with, so the challenges are big on this one. But Dog discovers a new source; "Facebook".

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mano-a-Mano
programme.desc: Back in Colorado, Dog's on the hunt for a runner with more than a decade's worth of trouble with the law. But the fugitive's friends and family are reluctant to help Dog bring him in.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Road Show: Where Mercy is Shown
programme.desc: After releasing the second part of his autobiography, Dog and his family traveled across America, and this very special episode offers an intimate portrait of both the public and private moments of that journey.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Comeback Kid
programme.desc: Dog is back in Colorado chasing a young man with a taste for trouble. He's fled to Texas but with his family's house on the line Dog is willing to try a risky strategy.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Tent City
programme.desc: Today's hunt takes Dog far from the glittering hotels of Waikiki to the parts of Hawaii tourist rarely see, Oahu's ramshackle tent cities. The team searches for a woman who has lost almost everything, her home, her family and her spirit.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Dead of Night
programme.desc: Dog's good friend and fellow bondsman Chris is running out of time. He has only days to find his fugitive or risk losing his business. In his hunt Dog confronts duplicitous tipsters, vicious attack dogs, and hostile neighbors.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Best of . . .
programme.desc: The bounty-hunter adventures of Duane "Dog" Chapman and his Posse are chronicled in this one hour "Best Of" special, featuring superlative memorable moments from the previous seven seasons.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Montrose Files: The Million Dollar Man Pt. 1
programme.desc: Dog launches a high stake hunt through the desolate and dangerous mountain landscape of western Colorado in pursuit of a gun-loving survivalist with a million dollar bond on his head. Will Dog's plan of using brains over brawn work?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Montrose Files: The Million Dollar Man Pt. 2
programme.desc: Once in Montrose, Dog discovers that the million dollar fugitive is not the young bondsman's only problem. Dog and Beth make it their mission to both clean up the mess and teach him the fundamentals of bondsmanship.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Montrose Files: Round the Clock
programme.desc: Dog is committed to saving his new friend's bail bonding business, and now must race against time to bring a rogues gallery to justice in the High Sierra mountain town of Montrose, CO.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Montrose Files: And Then There Were None
programme.desc: With four outlaws still on the lam, Dog sets out to bring 'em in. As day turns into night and with the darkness and the danger mounting, an undaunted Dog and team plan late night hits on the riskiest of locations--their targets' homes.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Oh Brother, Where Art Thou?
programme.desc: With a long record of violence and abuse and weighing in at over 200lbs, Dog's target for the day does not sound like a gentle giant. When the trail grows cold Dog turns up the heat on the fugitive's brother and sister.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Cap and Gown
programme.desc: Friend of the family, Kili, is joining the team to help track down a runner on the Hawaiian island of Maui. This is not the only thing on their schedule, because after the hunt, Kili has to hurry off to his college graduation ceremony!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: And Baby Makes Three
programme.desc: Leland has to attend a Lamaze class before he can join the hunt--another Chapman is on the way! But when Dog starts to go after this accused jewelry thief without his fastest son, he learns that this fugitive puts the "R" in runner.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Tender Trap
programme.desc: When Dog discovers today's prey is a notorious ladies man, he knows just how to lure him in. The trap includes a suggestive phone call, a motel rendezvous, and a crew of bounty hunters waiting in the next room ready to break up the party!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Greed is Good
programme.desc: Today's fugitive is accused of assaulting a police officer, so Dog and the team are not taking any chances. Dog has to play on his target's greed and deploy some modern technology to set a trap for this runner.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Baby's Back in Town
programme.desc: Dog tries to nab a fugitive, named Wayne, by calling and telling him that he's won a new vacuum cleaner and he should stick around to get it. Dog then sends his daughter, Lyssa, to "deliver" the vacuum cleaner and lure Wayne out of his house.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Surprise! Surprise!
Dog The Bounty Hunter: No Ice in Paradise
programme.desc: Dog and his team fight the war on ice-crystal methamphetamine-on many fronts. They appear on a special anti-drug float in a parade. Then they go after bail-jumping Pana, a convicted drug dealer.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Fathers in Law
programme.desc: Hunting down a fugitive known as "Bozo," Dog gets help from an unexpected source, Bozo's father-in-law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bosco the Clown
programme.desc: Dog and the team get a big surprise after they track down Bosco, a fugitive who they believe is addicted to methamphetamines. They discover he's off drugs, settling into a normal life with a new girlfriend, and is very friendly.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Brother's Keeper
programme.desc: Leland has a full plate of fugitives in Kona, and the whole family heads to the Big Island to help.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mama's Boys
programme.desc: Dog visits his mother's grave for inspiration before heading out to find Frankie, a violent fugitive hiding in the jungle. The spirit of Ma Chapman seems to help when Dog finds an unusual ally; Frankie's mother.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Lost in Paradise
programme.desc: Dog lectures high school students about the dangers of drugs before going after Joseph, a dangerous fugitive who won't be easy to capture.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Coaching Day
